{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96b3137c-ca5d-4367-9061-b0558d6e41ea","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9bc3bc35-6d65-46a4-8c2b-bfa1c597c7c2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"7C10:203FDB:27F6E67:2C4454A:69F946E2"},"id":"ae2e3835-3708-47cd-84c2-11a5d84b7c47","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:24:55.167Z","parentId":"a3ec3b6a-d78e-4b1b-958c-cefd5a26fd66"}
